  "title": "Mold Design & Process Engineer - WCAN",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Develop, document, and support the fabrication of high-precision plastic injection tooling and molded components for manufacturing.</li><li>Assist the Program team during new project quotations by providing accurate DFM (Design for Manufacturing) analysis to ensure tooling and product meet quality standards.</li><li>Collaborate with customers on DFM and mold concept reviews, addressing technical requirements and concerns.</li><li>Support the Tooling Department by conducting internal tooling design and DFM reviews prior to tool launch.</li><li>Assist Production in molding process optimization, implementing manufacturing fixtures and automation to enhance reliability and efficiency.</li><li>Support the Quality Team in designing and fabricating test and measurement fixtures.</li><li>Coordinate mold trials, troubleshoot tooling and molded parts, and implement engineering changes to ensure smooth production with required quality standards.</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>Strong technical and analytical skills with a keen interest in problem-solving.</li><li>Self-motivated team player with excellent interpersonal and communication skills.</li><li>Experience or knowledge in engineering design, manufacturing processes, or tooling is an advantage.</li><li>Proficient in 3D CAD or other engineering design software.</li></ul><p><br /></p><p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p><p><br /></p><p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p><p>EA License No: 20C0270</p><p>EA Personnel: Nyon Hock Sen (Aden)</p><p>EA Personnel Reg No: R24124070</p>",
